  "texts": [
    "For RLVR, we use the default GRPO implementation in verl without modification, with the reward given by binary ground-truth verifier.",
    "For RL-Logit, we extend verl with a custom reward function that computes the scalar reward from the policy logits on expert answers conditioned on the question and generated CoT tokens.",
    "To stabilize training and avoid vanishing or exploding rewards, we use two reward variants:",
    "• Log-probability variant: max(0.1 × log π θ (a ⋆ | q, z), -1.0)",
    "• Perplexity variant: 10.0 × exp(mean(log π θ (a ⋆ | q, z)))"
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}